WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:03.971
Christian.
Are you anywhere
in the Smoky Mountains?

00:04.004 --> 00:06.174
Birch Mountain Resort.
Shit!

00:06.207 --> 00:07.708
[ Sighs ]
I think she's got you.

00:07.741 --> 00:09.343
I'm sorry, Letty.

00:09.377 --> 00:11.412
I told you
to disappear.

00:11.445 --> 00:13.681
Agent Lashever: Drop the gun.
You're under arrest.

00:13.714 --> 00:15.249
FBI.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.152
Javier: Letty.

00:18.186 --> 00:19.820
Let him go!

00:19.853 --> 00:21.722
Ah!

00:23.091 --> 00:26.727
This was not the plan.
Let her go!

00:26.760 --> 00:28.796
**

00:30.030 --> 00:37.671
**

00:37.705 --> 00:41.275
Accessory
to attempted murder --

00:41.309 --> 00:44.044
That's 30 years,

00:44.078 --> 00:47.681
15 with good behavior.

00:47.715 --> 00:52.019
Be lucky if I ever
see Jacob again.

00:52.052 --> 00:55.256
You will see him.

00:55.289 --> 00:57.925
That'll be up to him,
won't it?

00:59.927 --> 01:05.133
Right when we got him
into school, too.

01:05.166 --> 01:07.801
We almost
made it work.

01:07.835 --> 01:11.272
Story of my life.

01:13.974 --> 01:15.743
Thanks, Mom.

01:15.776 --> 01:17.278
Agent Lashever:
[ Muffled ] You were talking
to Letty the whole time,

01:17.311 --> 01:18.812
and you never told me.

01:18.846 --> 01:20.214
Christian: [ Muffled ] No,
there was nothing to tell.

01:20.248 --> 01:21.715
She didn't tell me
where she was.

01:21.749 --> 01:23.417
She just told me that
she wasn't with Javier --

01:23.451 --> 01:24.985
And, by the way,
vacation?

01:25.018 --> 01:26.987
Your cabin?
Impressed?

01:27.020 --> 01:30.124
No! You're a pathological liar.
That's what you are.
Are the windows tinted?

01:30.158 --> 01:32.726
Probably.
Agent Lashever:
I'm an FBI agent.

01:32.760 --> 01:35.563
And now you know
how good an FBI agent I am.
Can that guy see us?

01:35.596 --> 01:37.331
Christian: Now I know
how sick you are.

01:37.365 --> 01:38.399
[ Chuckles ]
Okay.

01:38.432 --> 01:39.767
Letty:
Do you know him?

01:39.800 --> 01:41.101
His name is Teo.

01:41.135 --> 01:43.971
He was my friend,
growing up in Buenos Aires.

01:44.004 --> 01:45.573
What is he doing here?

01:45.606 --> 01:48.075
Probably
trying to kill me.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.310
**

01:49.343 --> 01:50.811
Come on, Woodhill.

01:50.844 --> 01:53.080
I'm not
doing this again.

01:53.113 --> 01:54.315
Shotgun
for your trouble?

01:54.348 --> 01:57.618
We know someone
wants to kill me.

01:57.651 --> 02:01.322
And we know
it's whoever killed Silk.

02:01.355 --> 02:03.591
Well, nobody
can touch you now.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.326
Christian:
Don't ever call me.

02:05.359 --> 02:07.328
Don't ever show up
at my house.

02:07.361 --> 02:08.529
I don't ever want
to see you again.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.097
Do you understand me?

02:10.130 --> 02:12.366
Agent Lashever: We're both
going to Asheville, dude.

02:12.400 --> 02:15.603
What are you gonna do --
Uber alongside?

02:15.636 --> 02:17.538
Open the back door.
I want to say goodbye to Letty.

02:17.571 --> 02:19.139
Get in the front
and ride with us.

02:19.173 --> 02:20.441
Open the door!

02:20.474 --> 02:21.942
[ Van door slides open ]

02:21.975 --> 02:23.143
[ Sighs ]

02:23.177 --> 02:25.279
I'm so sorry.

02:25.313 --> 02:27.715
I had no idea.

02:27.748 --> 02:29.883
It's okay.

02:29.917 --> 02:31.219
**

02:31.252 --> 02:33.821
Come with.
There's a bar.

02:33.854 --> 02:37.124
You heard her --
Come with.

02:37.157 --> 02:41.829
**

02:41.862 --> 02:44.698
[ Mouthing ]
Please help.

02:44.732 --> 02:49.136
**

02:49.169 --> 02:51.572
* Hard time forgiving

02:51.605 --> 02:54.375
* Even harder forgetting

02:54.408 --> 02:56.544
* Before you do something

02:56.577 --> 02:59.146
* You might regret, friend

02:59.179 --> 03:01.815
* Bricks are caving in

03:01.849 --> 03:04.151
* Oh, how sweet this sin

03:04.184 --> 03:06.820
* I left you the keys

03:06.854 --> 03:09.156
* You won't let me in

03:09.189 --> 03:11.559
* Hard time forgiving

03:11.592 --> 03:14.328
* Even harder forgetting

03:14.362 --> 03:16.597
* Before you do something

03:16.630 --> 03:20.167
* You might regret, friend

03:20.200 --> 03:22.870
[ Wind blowing ]

03:25.205 --> 03:28.876
[ Liquid trickling ]

03:34.915 --> 03:36.617
[ Sighs ]

03:38.586 --> 03:41.622
[ Exhales ]

03:41.655 --> 03:43.257
[ Whispering ]
I thought we were

03:43.291 --> 03:45.459
on vacation
at her cabin.

03:45.493 --> 03:49.697
Turns out
it was an Airbnb.

03:49.730 --> 03:52.232
She told me that
her mom used to give her

03:52.266 --> 03:56.036
baths in the kitchen sink
when she was a baby.

03:56.069 --> 04:01.074
What kind of a person
lies like that?

04:01.108 --> 04:02.710
I lie like that.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.978
[ Normal voice ]
But you're not mean.

04:05.012 --> 04:06.714
Thanks.

04:06.747 --> 04:09.417
She is so mean.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.218
I'm sorry, Letty.

04:11.251 --> 04:14.322
I -- I can't stay
in this car.

04:14.355 --> 04:17.157
So you're finally
giving up on me.

04:17.190 --> 04:20.528
No.
Never.

04:22.496 --> 04:28.402
But -- But what can
I realistically do?

04:28.436 --> 04:30.137
Just be here.

04:30.170 --> 04:31.805
Okay.

04:31.839 --> 04:34.074
Well...

04:34.107 --> 04:37.345
If you have
to go back to jail,

04:37.378 --> 04:42.416
it's very Letty of you
to be driven in a limo.

04:42.450 --> 04:44.117
Seriously,
what is this thing?

04:44.151 --> 04:45.653
I don't know.

04:45.686 --> 04:46.987
She says
she doesn't like

04:47.020 --> 04:49.357
the "basic shit"
that the FBI gives 'em.

04:49.390 --> 04:51.191
[ Slow-tempo music plays
over television ]

04:51.224 --> 04:52.760
So, you've been arrested.

04:52.793 --> 04:54.495
And if you're watching this,

04:54.528 --> 04:58.699
you've been arrested by me,
Special Agent Rhonda Lashever.

04:58.732 --> 05:02.836
You are my prisoner
and I am your captor,

05:02.870 --> 05:04.672
but if you follow
my simple rules,

05:04.705 --> 05:07.808
your voyage into
the criminal-justice system

05:07.841 --> 05:10.644
will be as safe,
smooth, and painless

05:10.678 --> 05:13.180
as bacon through a goose.
What the fuck?

05:13.213 --> 05:16.283
Agent Backup: Got to say,
I wasn't sure about
the whole stalker plan,

05:16.316 --> 05:18.619
but, damn, it worked.

05:18.652 --> 05:22.222
You don't have to tell me
things I know.

05:22.255 --> 05:25.526
Sorry. I just mean
it went really well overall.

05:25.559 --> 05:27.127
Considering
you just had me.

05:27.160 --> 05:29.630
Are you trying
to take credit for this?
No, sorry --

05:29.663 --> 05:31.632
Because in case you haven't
looked in a mirror,

05:31.665 --> 05:34.001
you got beaten up.

05:34.034 --> 05:36.370
Props for that tattoo,
though.

05:36.404 --> 05:37.838
Looks legit.
Yeah.

05:37.871 --> 05:41.241
Yeah, they said
it stays on for a month.
Yikes.

05:41.274 --> 05:43.644
Hope it doesn't peel off
little by little --

05:43.677 --> 05:44.678
Won't be cute.

05:44.712 --> 05:46.246
[ Thunder rumbles ]

05:46.279 --> 05:47.981
Shit.
[ Car beeping ]

05:48.015 --> 05:50.584
Did you just slow down
because of a little rain?
[ Beeping stops ]

05:50.618 --> 05:52.486
I'm not great
with bad weather.

05:52.520 --> 05:53.521
Oh!

05:53.554 --> 05:54.655
So you're
an FBI agent,

05:54.688 --> 05:56.056
but only
if it's nice outside.

05:56.089 --> 05:58.559
If we get into an accident,
they could run away.

05:58.592 --> 06:00.428
You're going
15 under the limit!

06:00.461 --> 06:02.095
It...

06:04.565 --> 06:08.769
I was stuck by lightning
when I was 12, okay?

06:10.103 --> 06:12.172
That explains
your narcissism.

06:12.205 --> 06:13.240
Step on the gas.

06:13.273 --> 06:14.942
[ Thunder rumbles ]
[ Engine revs ]

06:14.975 --> 06:18.679
This concludes my advice
and your instructions.

06:18.712 --> 06:21.449
Ignore at your own expense.

06:21.482 --> 06:22.683
[ Bottle cork pops ]
Ha!

06:22.716 --> 06:23.717
Ha, ha!

06:23.751 --> 06:25.185
Love you, Mary Ann!

06:25.218 --> 06:28.355
Had you there for a second.
Yes, I did!

06:28.388 --> 06:31.224
Let the bachelorette weekend
begin!

06:33.494 --> 06:34.728
I can't believe
she's the reason

06:34.762 --> 06:36.864
we're going
to prison.

06:36.897 --> 06:39.266
Well,
she's not the reason.

06:39.299 --> 06:42.269
[ Chuckles ]
Had you for a second.

06:42.302 --> 06:44.538
Not really.

06:44.572 --> 06:46.540
But I like your car.

06:46.574 --> 06:49.710
Not a car --
It's a Sprinter.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.212
I like your Sprinter.

06:52.245 --> 06:55.716
Luxury conversion
by moi.

06:55.749 --> 06:58.586
Hashtag SprinterLife.

06:58.619 --> 07:00.120
I want one.

07:00.153 --> 07:02.623
I don't see that happening,
Ms. Raines, do you?

07:02.656 --> 07:04.124
You're in charge.

07:04.157 --> 07:06.226
I am, and I don't
see that happening.

07:06.259 --> 07:07.227
[ Thunder rumbles ]

07:07.260 --> 07:10.731
How come Antonio Banderas
is so quiet?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.733
He's never been
to prison.

07:12.766 --> 07:13.967
Which is a miracle,

07:14.001 --> 07:16.737
considering how dumb he was
to buy a gun

07:16.770 --> 07:19.973
and then carve his name
into it.

07:20.007 --> 07:21.909
It was
a Christmas gift.

07:21.942 --> 07:24.411
Sure it was --
to yourself.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.980
If you know what you really want
for Christmas,

07:27.014 --> 07:30.918
you got to get it
for yourself, right?

07:30.951 --> 07:32.953
This is what
I got for myself.

07:32.986 --> 07:34.822
[ Recorded gun cocks, gunshot ]

07:34.855 --> 07:37.424
Ha, ha!
Sound machine.

07:37.457 --> 07:41.995
You ever think about
getting a gun that
says "hit man" on it?

07:42.029 --> 07:44.031
[ Canned laughter ]

07:44.064 --> 07:45.098
[ Laughs ]

07:45.132 --> 07:46.600
[ Thunder crashes,
tires screech ]

07:46.634 --> 07:49.770
[ Car beeping ]
Jesus Christ,
Agent Backup.

07:49.803 --> 07:53.607
[ Beeping stops ]
You're responsible
for some very precious cargo,

07:53.641 --> 07:55.976
and all of the people
inside of it.

07:56.009 --> 07:57.177
I think
you should thank

07:57.210 --> 07:58.779
the lane-departure
warning system

07:58.812 --> 08:02.816
for handling your
untreated weather PTSD.

08:04.217 --> 08:07.020
I'd appreciate it if you
wouldn't talk about that
in front of other people.

08:07.054 --> 08:08.789
The rest of your life
will appreciate it

08:08.822 --> 08:10.924
if you see
a therapist.

08:12.693 --> 08:14.361
Wait, "Agent Backup"?

08:14.394 --> 08:15.495
I have a name.

08:15.529 --> 08:17.565
And nobody
wants to know it.

08:17.598 --> 08:18.832
[ Thunder rumbles ]

08:18.866 --> 08:20.400
How long have you guys
been partners?

08:20.433 --> 08:23.136
Are you kidding?
We're not partners.

08:23.170 --> 08:26.173
Agent Backup just graduated
from our training program

08:26.206 --> 08:28.141
a couple
of months ago.

08:28.175 --> 08:30.578
So he's kind of like
one of those sad newbies

08:30.611 --> 08:32.813
who stands behind
the waitress,

08:32.846 --> 08:35.315
or a...baby pony

08:35.348 --> 08:37.184
who hasn't quite
figured out how to walk --

08:37.217 --> 08:40.020
stumbling around,
easily startled,

08:40.053 --> 08:44.257
marking time by the distance
between nursing sessions.

08:44.291 --> 08:51.164
**

08:51.198 --> 08:53.000
I cannot believe
you did this.

08:53.033 --> 08:55.335
Rob, just pack.

08:55.368 --> 08:57.204
Do you have the keys
for both cars?

08:57.237 --> 08:59.039
Yeah, but how could you
not talk it out,

08:59.072 --> 09:00.507
hear his side
of things?

09:00.540 --> 09:01.775
His side of things

09:01.809 --> 09:03.343
is that people pay him
to commit murder.

09:03.376 --> 09:05.412
See? Now, that's
your interpretation.

09:05.445 --> 09:08.782
But maybe he's like Batman
or something.

09:08.816 --> 09:10.050
Like a good bad guy.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.285
Yeah, I'm sure that's
what Letty would say.

09:12.319 --> 09:16.223
Well, now you have to visit her
in jail to ask her.

09:16.256 --> 09:19.359
That wasn't supposed to happen.
She did that to herself.

09:19.392 --> 09:23.530
I swear, she is the dumbest
smart person I know.
[ Suitcases zipping ]

09:23.563 --> 09:27.034
**

09:27.067 --> 09:28.401
Give me the keys
to the silver.

09:28.435 --> 09:30.437
You drive theirs.

09:30.470 --> 09:38.045
**

09:38.078 --> 09:39.579
Agent Lashever:
Diesel!

09:39.613 --> 09:41.114
Oh, shit.
Sorry.

09:41.148 --> 09:42.883
You work for the FBI.

09:42.916 --> 09:45.886
If you can't follow
simple instructions,

09:45.919 --> 09:47.821
I suggest you go
into the bathroom

09:47.855 --> 09:49.556
and take a hard look
at yourself

09:49.589 --> 09:52.960
in the polished-aluminum
paper-towel dispenser...
[ Grunts ]

09:52.993 --> 09:55.128
...they have
instead of a mirror.

09:55.162 --> 09:57.998
**

09:58.031 --> 09:59.566
I don't think
this is a real thing,

09:59.599 --> 10:02.736
like it was the first time
she tried to get you.

10:02.770 --> 10:04.104
How is it not real?

10:04.137 --> 10:06.006
Where's
the SWAT team?

10:06.039 --> 10:09.109
Lashever, an intern,
a prom limo?

10:09.142 --> 10:11.444
Javier's
her white whale.

10:11.478 --> 10:12.579
I'm who?

10:12.612 --> 10:15.282
Her white whale.
It's from "Moby Dick."

10:15.315 --> 10:17.417
It's your biggest
sworn enemy,

10:17.450 --> 10:19.820
the arch-rival
you can't defeat,

10:19.853 --> 10:22.522
stands in the way
of everything.

10:22.555 --> 10:23.757
And that's me?

10:23.791 --> 10:26.159
Woodhill.

10:26.193 --> 10:28.696
Let's check out
the jerky situation.

10:28.729 --> 10:31.598
**

10:31.631 --> 10:33.333
[ Glass rattles ]

10:33.366 --> 10:34.868
**

10:34.902 --> 10:37.504
Close the door.

10:37.537 --> 10:41.308
[ Van door slides closed ]

10:41.341 --> 10:51.618
**

10:51.651 --> 10:52.986
If this was a real job,

10:53.020 --> 10:55.155
she would've taken us
to the closest prison.

10:55.188 --> 10:56.690
If I am
her white whale,

10:56.724 --> 10:58.859
she wants to show me off
at the office in Asheville.

10:58.892 --> 11:01.962
I'm sorry, but you're
not a big-enough deal
to be a white whale.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.831
There's got to be
something else.

11:03.864 --> 11:05.332
[ Scoffs ]

11:05.365 --> 11:06.533
I'm serious.

11:06.566 --> 11:08.035
I know.

11:08.068 --> 11:10.070
You never give up.

11:10.103 --> 11:11.404
Are you giving up?

11:11.438 --> 11:14.975
I am in handcuffs,
and I am not a magician.

11:15.008 --> 11:25.052
**

11:25.085 --> 11:28.421
You're not a magician,
either.

11:28.455 --> 11:31.658
**

11:31.691 --> 11:33.994
Letty, when we go
to prison --

11:34.027 --> 11:35.162
There's got to be
a way out of this.

11:35.195 --> 11:36.496
When we go to prison,

11:36.529 --> 11:38.065
they will ask you
to testify against me.

11:38.098 --> 11:39.733
No, no.
And you should.

11:39.767 --> 11:41.068
Why would you say that?

11:41.101 --> 11:42.335
Because I am thinking
about your life,

11:42.369 --> 11:43.670
and I'm thinking
about Jacob.

11:43.703 --> 11:46.106
So am I, and the last time
I had to choose

11:46.139 --> 11:48.541
between you and Jacob,
I got both of you.

11:48.575 --> 11:50.210
Well...

11:50.243 --> 11:51.879
Lightning doesn't
strike twice.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.246
Yes, it does.

11:53.280 --> 11:55.883
It doesn't strike
in the same place twice.

11:55.916 --> 11:58.852
[ Sighs ]

11:58.886 --> 12:02.722
**

12:02.756 --> 12:04.792
We are
in the same place.

12:04.825 --> 12:09.797
**

12:09.830 --> 12:12.132
[ Slow-tempo music playing ]
What do you want?

12:12.165 --> 12:15.903
Just a sparkling water.

12:15.936 --> 12:18.806
[ Music continues ]

12:18.839 --> 12:20.440
Ah.

12:20.473 --> 12:21.541
What do you want?

12:21.574 --> 12:25.145
Coconut water.

12:25.178 --> 12:28.048
[ Beverage case opens, closes ]

12:28.081 --> 12:32.719
Pink Gatorade.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.555
And a...

12:35.588 --> 12:38.058
Mountain Dew Code Red.

12:38.091 --> 12:42.996
I appreciate you babysitting
those losers back there.

12:43.030 --> 12:45.065
They're not...
[ Sighs ]

12:45.098 --> 12:47.567
Look,
I don't know Javier,

12:47.600 --> 12:49.903
but Letty's not
a loser.
Yes, she is.

12:49.937 --> 12:52.239
She's the reason Javier
got away from me the first time.

12:52.272 --> 12:54.908
You don't know that.
Oh, I have a strong feeling
I do know that.

12:54.942 --> 12:56.409
I think
she interfered.

12:56.443 --> 12:58.278
I think
she tipped him off.
You have no proof.

12:58.311 --> 12:59.913
I have proof
she pulled a gun on me.

12:59.947 --> 13:02.082
Okay,
and that's not good,

13:02.115 --> 13:05.318
but do you think
you could take a step back?

13:05.352 --> 13:06.653
Isn't this
all about Javier?

13:06.686 --> 13:08.856
Do you really need to be
putting Letty in jail?

13:08.889 --> 13:10.257
Do you have a thing
for her?

13:10.290 --> 13:11.825
"A thing"?
No.

13:11.859 --> 13:13.426
What kind of thing?

13:13.460 --> 13:15.929
A thing for taking care
of lost causes...
[ Sighs ]

13:15.963 --> 13:17.297
...because that
grosses me out,

13:17.330 --> 13:18.866
and I seriously
don't need that.

13:18.899 --> 13:20.267
I'm not a lost cause,

13:20.300 --> 13:21.801
so if what you want
is a lost cause,

13:21.835 --> 13:22.970
I think it's probably

13:23.003 --> 13:24.271
a good idea
we're breaking up.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.439
We're already broken up.
I broke up with you.

13:26.473 --> 13:27.607
Fake news.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.943
Get some Corn Nuts
and meet me at the jerky.

13:29.977 --> 13:32.679
[ Music continues ]

13:32.712 --> 13:34.381
[ Thunder rumbles ]

13:34.414 --> 13:36.816
Rob: I think you should
call Lashever.

13:36.850 --> 13:38.051
Estelle: [ Through speaker ]
The FBI agent?

13:38.085 --> 13:39.286
She's cool.

13:39.319 --> 13:40.954
We bonded
over "The Bodyguard,"

13:40.988 --> 13:42.322
so she's not a monster.

13:42.355 --> 13:44.791
You know,
maybe she'll let Letty go.

13:44.824 --> 13:45.959
She won't.

13:45.993 --> 13:47.027
I tried.

13:47.060 --> 13:48.495
You saw me clawing at her

13:48.528 --> 13:50.898
when she took Letty
into her van.

13:50.931 --> 13:53.366
You can't stop trying.

13:53.400 --> 13:55.835
I've been trying
since she was born.

13:55.869 --> 13:59.306
Look, babe, I know you better
than anyone, okay?

13:59.339 --> 14:01.041
And I know
you're lying to me.

14:01.074 --> 14:04.077
Rob: And that's okay, because
I know why you're lying to me,

14:04.111 --> 14:06.914
'cause like I said,
I know you better than anyone.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.916
What you're
dealing with is --

14:08.949 --> 14:12.319
Look, there's -- there's two
parts to the brain, all right,

14:12.352 --> 14:14.587
the conscious
and the subconscious,

14:14.621 --> 14:16.223
and while you are
consciously wanting

14:16.256 --> 14:17.757
to get your daughter free,

14:17.790 --> 14:19.726
the other part --
the -- the sub part --

14:19.759 --> 14:22.329
is actually worried about
what she'll do on her own,

14:22.362 --> 14:25.165
seeing as how every time
she gets out of prison,

14:25.198 --> 14:27.700
she seems to get herself
back in again.

14:27.734 --> 14:29.402
But even deeper than that,

14:29.436 --> 14:32.940
what you're wondering about
in the sub-subconscious

14:32.973 --> 14:38.411
is whether or not all these
impulses that Letty suffers from

14:38.445 --> 14:42.182
are really due to her childhood
and how you raised her.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.351
I guess what I'm trying to say

14:44.384 --> 14:48.188
is I don't really think
that you're mad at Letty.

14:48.221 --> 14:52.459
I think you're mad at yourself.

14:52.492 --> 14:55.095
Hello?

14:55.128 --> 14:57.197
Hello?

14:57.230 --> 14:58.765
Hi.
I lost you.

14:58.798 --> 15:01.201
What?
Where'd you lose me?

15:01.234 --> 15:02.635
I was making my point.

15:02.669 --> 15:05.038
You said you know me better
than anyone.

15:05.072 --> 15:06.273
Shit.

15:06.306 --> 15:08.241
You missed
my whole damn speech!

15:08.275 --> 15:11.911
Sorry, I must've gone
through a dead spot.

15:11.945 --> 15:13.880
Oh.

15:13.913 --> 15:16.883
Well...
[ Sighs ]

15:16.916 --> 15:18.285
Now I lost
the thought.

15:18.318 --> 15:20.820
It'll come back to you.

15:20.853 --> 15:22.055
[ Speaker beeps ]

15:22.089 --> 15:23.456
**

15:23.490 --> 15:25.725
[ Man speaking indistinctly ]

15:25.758 --> 15:28.128
[ Police radio chatter ]

15:28.161 --> 15:32.932
**

15:32.966 --> 15:35.668
[ Window whirs ]

15:35.702 --> 15:37.470
This way, please.
The road is closed.

15:37.504 --> 15:38.671
It's not safe
up ahead.

15:38.705 --> 15:40.073
There's a huge amount
of flooding.

15:40.107 --> 15:41.174
Thank you, officer.

15:41.208 --> 15:43.743
Hold on!

15:43.776 --> 15:47.114
I'm transporting
two very dangerous prisoners,

15:47.147 --> 15:48.415
and I assure you,

15:48.448 --> 15:51.451
this vehicle is capable
of fording the river.

15:51.484 --> 15:52.819
Sorry, ma'am,
the road's closed.

15:52.852 --> 15:55.688
How long
before it's clear?
No idea.

15:55.722 --> 15:57.590
How deep is the water?

15:57.624 --> 15:58.758
Three feet.

15:58.791 --> 16:01.694
Not an issue for this vehicle.
We're going through.

16:01.728 --> 16:03.430
Move the...thing.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.698
I need to run this
by my supervisor.

16:05.732 --> 16:07.334
Go up there,

16:07.367 --> 16:08.768
tell her
this is dangerous.

16:08.801 --> 16:10.603
Her car could be wrecked,
we could die --

16:10.637 --> 16:11.938
whatever
you need to say.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.774
Letty.
Just do it.

16:14.807 --> 16:18.178
[ Window whirs ]

16:18.211 --> 16:19.479
[ Sighs ]

16:19.512 --> 16:23.783
Hi. Uh, isn't this
a little dangerous?

16:23.816 --> 16:25.852
I think we should do
what the cop says.

16:25.885 --> 16:29.456
I outrank cops.
Cops have to do what I say.

16:29.489 --> 16:31.224
Your video said
this journey would be

16:31.258 --> 16:32.525
smooth, safe,
and painless.

16:32.559 --> 16:34.827
You still think
that video was real?

16:34.861 --> 16:36.629
I think we should
just turn around

16:36.663 --> 16:38.298
and grab a motel
for the night.

16:38.331 --> 16:39.632
[ Sighs ]
What is your problem?

16:39.666 --> 16:41.134
You afraid
of a little mud?

16:41.168 --> 16:43.070
No, but...

16:43.103 --> 16:44.237
[ Softly ]
Tow truck.

16:44.271 --> 16:45.305
Accident.

16:45.338 --> 16:47.140
Embarrassing.

16:47.174 --> 16:49.809
**

16:49.842 --> 16:50.977
All I'm saying is that

16:51.010 --> 16:53.546
God forbid something
should happen to your van

16:53.580 --> 16:55.715
and it has
to be towed in.

16:55.748 --> 16:58.885
How would that look
to everybody in the office?

16:58.918 --> 17:04.324
**

17:04.357 --> 17:05.858
[ Knock on window ]

17:05.892 --> 17:08.561
Sorry, Agent Lash--
Where's
the closest motel?

17:08.595 --> 17:10.830
Uh, there's a Motel 6
and Holiday Inn Express

17:10.863 --> 17:12.031
a few miles back.

17:12.065 --> 17:13.733
Roll up the window,
turn around,

17:13.766 --> 17:15.335
take us to the H.I.E.

17:15.368 --> 17:16.569
[ Gasps softly ]

17:16.603 --> 17:18.771
[ Thunder rumbles ]
[ Window whirs ]

17:25.312 --> 17:27.547
Agent Lashever:
You ever have the cinnamon rolls
at H.I.E., Javier?

17:27.580 --> 17:28.948
Javier:
Can't say that I have.

17:28.981 --> 17:31.184
Woman: Thanks.

17:31.218 --> 17:33.186
Man: Welcome to
the Holiday Inn Express.

17:33.220 --> 17:34.554
Do you have
a reservation?

17:34.587 --> 17:37.890
You don't need to give me
the whole spiel...Flash.

17:37.924 --> 17:40.093
I am a founding member.

17:40.127 --> 17:41.128
Of what?

17:41.161 --> 17:44.131
Of H.I.E. Rewards.

17:44.164 --> 17:45.265
Two rooms adjoining,

17:45.298 --> 17:47.033
make mine
the handicapped suite.

17:47.066 --> 17:49.469
The -- I'm sorry,
we don't have any suites.

17:49.502 --> 17:50.970
All of our rooms
are the same.

17:51.003 --> 17:55.041
Let me let you in
on a little secret, Flash.

17:55.074 --> 17:59.412
The rooms for disabled guests
have larger entryways,

17:59.446 --> 18:02.549
bigger bathtubs,
and other amenities.

18:02.582 --> 18:03.783
Insiders call it
the Presidential Suite...

18:03.816 --> 18:05.152
[ Handcuffs rattle ]
...which you --

18:05.185 --> 18:07.654
Holy shit.

18:07.687 --> 18:09.922
Don't overreact,
Flash.

18:09.956 --> 18:11.891
This is classified, FBI,

18:11.924 --> 18:13.793
you know...protocol.

18:13.826 --> 18:15.762
Are they --
Are they dangerous?

18:15.795 --> 18:16.996
To me, no.

18:17.029 --> 18:18.565
To you, yeah.

18:18.598 --> 18:21.768
Just look what they did
to that idiot.

18:21.801 --> 18:25.605
**

18:25.638 --> 18:26.973
Don't worry, Flash.

18:27.006 --> 18:31.444
As long as I'm here,
the franchise is safe.

18:31.478 --> 18:33.313
[ Thunder rumbles ]

18:33.346 --> 18:34.781
What's happening?

18:34.814 --> 18:36.316
We got a flooded road
up ahead

18:36.349 --> 18:37.850
and a fallen tree
about a mile back.

18:37.884 --> 18:39.619
It could be a while.
Do you have food?

18:39.652 --> 18:42.255
We need
to get through here.

18:42.289 --> 18:43.756
No can do.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.825
Please pull up and park
like everyone else is doing.

18:45.858 --> 18:47.427
Why can't
we just go back?

18:47.460 --> 18:48.995
Tree fell down.

18:49.028 --> 18:51.364
We just came from that way.
We didn't see any tree.

18:51.398 --> 18:53.333
Since then.
[ Window whirs ]

18:53.366 --> 18:57.003
Oh.

18:57.036 --> 18:59.172
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

18:59.206 --> 19:02.775
[ Keys jingle ]

19:02.809 --> 19:06.546
Why is it impossible
to turn on TVs in hotels?

19:06.579 --> 19:08.848
Because drinking
makes you bad at things?

19:08.881 --> 19:11.184
Sometimes it makes me
good at things.

19:11.218 --> 19:13.019
Spoken like
a true alcoholic.

19:14.487 --> 19:16.956
Yeah.
You don't drink?

19:16.989 --> 19:20.460
Never had a drop.

19:20.493 --> 19:23.230
Is there any way
I can get a martini?

19:23.263 --> 19:24.664
You're joking, right?

19:24.697 --> 19:26.899
I never joke
about drinking.

19:26.933 --> 19:28.968
**

19:29.001 --> 19:31.804
Help me, Rhonda.

19:31.838 --> 19:33.573
This is our last night
of freedom.

19:33.606 --> 19:35.074
Don't we get
a last meal?

19:35.107 --> 19:36.643
You're not being executed.

19:36.676 --> 19:37.877
It feels like we are.

19:37.910 --> 19:40.480
Good.

19:40.513 --> 19:41.914
What would you want?

19:41.948 --> 19:43.316
Vodka.

19:43.350 --> 19:45.184
[ Laughs ]
Me, too.

19:45.218 --> 19:47.554
Me three.

19:47.587 --> 19:49.155
We're stuck
for the night.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.657
They're in handcuffs.

19:50.690 --> 19:53.760
What's the harm
in a couple martinis?

19:53.793 --> 19:56.263
**

19:56.296 --> 19:57.497
[ Sniffs ]

19:57.530 --> 20:02.269
[ Thunder rumbles ]

20:02.302 --> 20:04.170
**

20:04.203 --> 20:06.172
One martini each.

20:06.205 --> 20:07.674
Oh, my God.

20:07.707 --> 20:08.841
Agent Lashever:
Don't swear.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.209
Just go out
to the Sprinter

20:10.243 --> 20:11.944
and get the stuff
from the bar.

20:11.978 --> 20:13.513
What stuff?

20:13.546 --> 20:14.947
Have you never had
a martini?

20:14.981 --> 20:16.048
He doesn't drink.

20:16.082 --> 20:17.684
Are you serious?

20:17.717 --> 20:19.686
I don't drink.
That's a good thing.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.788
Take Ms. Raines with you.

20:21.821 --> 20:23.523
She's an alcoholic.
She'll know what to get.

20:23.556 --> 20:25.057
I'll watch Javier
while you're gone,

20:25.091 --> 20:27.260
but I want to take a bath,
so make it quick.

20:27.294 --> 20:28.728
Christian,
you're on ice.

20:28.761 --> 20:34.367
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

20:34.401 --> 20:39.506
**

20:45.578 --> 20:47.013
[ Grunts ]

20:49.649 --> 20:52.385
[ Thunder crashes ]

20:52.419 --> 21:00.059
**

21:00.092 --> 21:02.261
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

21:02.295 --> 21:06.165
If you'd run,
I would've shot you.

21:11.804 --> 21:14.474
What am I getting,
again?

21:14.507 --> 21:16.576
Vodka.
[ Bottles clinking ]

21:16.609 --> 21:18.578
Vermouth,
the dry kind.

21:18.611 --> 21:20.179
Wait,
one thing at a time.

21:20.212 --> 21:22.014
[ Thunder rumbles ]

21:25.885 --> 21:30.823
[ Piano music playing
over television ]

21:30.857 --> 21:32.759
[ Softly ] Hey.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.461
Hey.

21:35.995 --> 21:38.331
The keys to the handcuffs

21:38.365 --> 21:40.967
are on
the backup guy's belt.

21:41.000 --> 21:42.301
And?

21:42.335 --> 21:44.270
And maybe
you can get them.

21:44.303 --> 21:45.638
And go to prison
with you?

21:45.672 --> 21:47.640
I'm just thinking
about Letty.

21:47.674 --> 21:49.942
Oh, really?

21:49.976 --> 21:52.479
At what point did you start
thinking about Letty?

21:52.512 --> 21:54.113
What do you mean?

21:54.146 --> 21:55.482
[ Whispering ]
I mean...

21:55.515 --> 21:57.550
nothing gets past her.

21:57.584 --> 22:00.520
So how is it that
a savvy woman like Letty

22:00.553 --> 22:02.655
got dragged
into your bullshit,

22:02.689 --> 22:04.657
with your
chosen profession?

22:04.691 --> 22:06.826
If you really love
someone,

22:06.859 --> 22:09.529
let them go, right?

22:11.764 --> 22:13.232
I tried.

22:13.265 --> 22:15.234
Maybe you should've
just done it.

22:15.267 --> 22:18.505
Look.

22:18.538 --> 22:21.541
I know I'm going to prison
for the rest of my life,

22:21.574 --> 22:23.309
but if Letty
goes back in,

22:23.342 --> 22:26.713
I don't know
if she will be okay.

22:26.746 --> 22:28.180
So can you talk
to your girlfriend

22:28.214 --> 22:29.348
and convince her
to let her go?

22:29.382 --> 22:31.718
It doesn't work
that way, dude.

22:31.751 --> 22:33.486
She may be
a little crazy,

22:33.520 --> 22:35.321
but she's still
an FBI agent.

22:35.354 --> 22:38.257
She can't just take a person
into federal custody

22:38.290 --> 22:39.526
and then let 'em go.

22:39.559 --> 22:43.430
There are laws.

22:43.463 --> 22:45.164
But I did try.

22:45.197 --> 22:46.699
[ Door opens ]

22:50.069 --> 22:51.438
[ Door closes ]

22:51.471 --> 22:53.239
Agent Lashever:
Set all this up in my room.

22:53.272 --> 22:56.075
The handicapped sink
doubles as a wet bar.

22:56.108 --> 22:58.511
[ Thunder rumbles ]

22:58.545 --> 23:03.182
[ Cocktail shaker rattles ]

23:03.215 --> 23:05.351
Whoo, look at you.

23:05.384 --> 23:07.887
Tom Cruise
in "Cocktail."

23:07.920 --> 23:10.022
Could you unwrap
those cups?
Hmm.

23:10.056 --> 23:11.891
Tom Cruise wouldn't
have asked his customers

23:11.924 --> 23:13.225
to do any of the work.

23:13.259 --> 23:15.027
If you uncuff me,
I can unwrap them.

23:15.061 --> 23:16.228
[ Chuckles ]

23:16.262 --> 23:17.764
That's very clever,
Ms. Raines.

23:17.797 --> 23:19.231
Every time you say
"Mrs. Raines,"

23:19.265 --> 23:21.133
it's like my ears
are being raped.

23:21.167 --> 23:22.635
Ms. Raines.

23:26.338 --> 23:28.641
Remind you
of getting drug tested?

23:33.446 --> 23:35.748
We have
a one-drink maximum

23:35.782 --> 23:38.751
here at Lashever's
Liquor Emporium.

23:38.785 --> 23:40.487
That goes for you, too,
Agent Backup.

23:40.520 --> 23:42.755
Agent Backup: I'm sorry,
but I'm not drinking.

23:42.789 --> 23:46.726
**

23:46.759 --> 23:50.329
Most favorite
and least favorite prison?

23:50.362 --> 23:52.999
Only a person who's
never been to prison

23:53.032 --> 23:54.066
would ask that.

23:54.100 --> 23:55.167
Jesus, Rhonda.

23:55.201 --> 23:57.637
It's not a time out,
it's prison.

23:57.670 --> 23:59.772
People lose
everything.

23:59.806 --> 24:01.608
You don't think
I get that?

24:01.641 --> 24:03.476
Actions have
consequences.

24:03.510 --> 24:06.112
She's had too many
slaps on the wrist.

24:06.145 --> 24:07.680
Time to up
the dosage.

24:07.714 --> 24:10.316
Federal prison
will be good for you.

24:10.349 --> 24:11.518
You'll come out better.

24:11.551 --> 24:13.820
I never
come out better.

24:13.853 --> 24:16.956
I've only
been better since...

24:18.324 --> 24:21.628
If I go back to prison,
I'll never really be good.

24:21.661 --> 24:24.296
I'll only ever
be managed.

24:24.330 --> 24:27.133
[ Thunder rumbling ]

24:27.166 --> 24:29.001
[ Scoffs ]

24:34.206 --> 24:36.208
[ Thunder crashes ]
Oh, my God!
Holy shit!

24:36.242 --> 24:39.846
[ Laughs ]
[ Panting ]

24:39.879 --> 24:54.661
**

24:54.694 --> 24:56.963
[ Thunder crashes ]
Oh, fuck me!

24:56.996 --> 24:58.531
[ Laughs ]

24:58.565 --> 24:59.566
[ Glass shatters ]
Ah!

24:59.599 --> 25:02.334
-[ Grunts ]
-Whoa!

25:02.368 --> 25:05.872
[ Wind whistling ]

25:05.905 --> 25:12.545
**

25:12.579 --> 25:19.986
[ Electricity buzzing ]

25:20.019 --> 25:23.355
**

25:23.389 --> 25:26.693
What the hell is that?

25:26.726 --> 25:30.329
I think it's a sign.

25:30.362 --> 25:32.398
[ Sign buzzes ]

25:32.431 --> 25:35.735
[ Thunder rumbles ]

25:35.768 --> 25:37.637
It is.

25:41.273 --> 25:42.374
At least we have
another room.

25:42.408 --> 25:44.543
But it's not
a presidential suite.

25:44.577 --> 25:46.012
I think we'll survive.

25:46.045 --> 25:48.047
He might not.

25:48.080 --> 25:50.016
[ Thunder rumbles, crashes ]

25:50.049 --> 25:51.550
[ Inhales sharply ]

25:51.584 --> 25:54.386
Backup!

25:54.420 --> 25:55.888
Say something.

25:55.922 --> 25:58.090
**

25:58.124 --> 26:00.960
He needs a drink.

26:03.395 --> 26:08.234
Shit, he's like Cameron
in "Ferris Bueller's Day Off."

26:08.267 --> 26:12.104
Drink.
That's a direct order.

26:25.517 --> 26:29.455
[ Forcefully ]
Can you take another sip?

26:32.458 --> 26:34.393
This is why I never wanted
to be a mother.

26:34.426 --> 26:36.428
Come on.

26:36.462 --> 26:37.596
Drink up.

26:37.630 --> 26:39.131
Hey, do you want
to play a game?

26:39.165 --> 26:42.969
It's a fun drinking game.
Come on.

26:43.002 --> 26:44.570
No.

26:44.603 --> 26:45.938
Ooh!
He speaks.

26:45.972 --> 26:48.107
Keep going.
Make him play.

26:48.140 --> 26:51.911
* Let's get
the rhythm of the feet *

26:51.944 --> 26:54.513
* Let's get the rhythm of

26:54.546 --> 26:56.615
I have
my pilot's license.

26:56.649 --> 26:57.784
I'm an amazing cook.

26:57.817 --> 26:59.285
My middle name
is Diego.

26:59.318 --> 27:00.619
Which one is the lie?

27:00.653 --> 27:02.454
You don't have
your pilot's license.

27:02.488 --> 27:04.590
Yes, he does.

27:04.623 --> 27:05.958
So now you drink.

27:05.992 --> 27:08.294
**

27:08.327 --> 27:10.129
* Hunh, smooth talker

27:10.162 --> 27:11.263
Can I ask
you something?

27:11.297 --> 27:12.699
* I'm a lover
No.

27:12.732 --> 27:14.633
* No disrespect, man
I was born in Charlotte.

27:14.667 --> 27:16.803
I am not circumcised.

27:16.836 --> 27:18.204
My name is Stewart.

27:18.237 --> 27:19.638
* I'm on the level
Stewart.

27:19.672 --> 27:21.607
* Ghost walker

27:21.640 --> 27:23.475
* Like the devil
* Hunh

27:23.509 --> 27:25.644
* Headbanger, go-getter

27:25.678 --> 27:28.981
How do you afford
that tricked-out ride
on your FBI salary?

27:29.015 --> 27:30.449
You don't know
what I make.

27:30.482 --> 27:32.819
I know
it's a government job.

27:32.852 --> 27:34.153
You know how much money

27:34.186 --> 27:37.623
we confiscate every year
from criminals like you?

27:37.656 --> 27:39.391
But you don't get
to keep it.

27:39.425 --> 27:40.626
No.

27:40.659 --> 27:43.629
All it does is collect dust
in sad closets.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.698
* Hunh, two sisters
Sad.

27:45.732 --> 27:48.400
Most people spend all
their money on children.

27:48.434 --> 27:50.036
I spend it
on luxury vans.

27:50.069 --> 27:51.170
* Like my mother

27:51.203 --> 27:53.973
I am an amazing
fisherman.

27:54.006 --> 27:55.842
I am an amazing
handyman.

27:55.875 --> 27:57.576
I am an amazing
hit man.

27:57.609 --> 28:01.981
You're not
an amazing fisherman.

28:02.014 --> 28:03.182
I am an amazing
fisherman.

28:03.215 --> 28:04.917
-Ohh!
-Yep.

28:04.951 --> 28:06.518
-Drink.
-Drink.

28:06.552 --> 28:08.687
Agent Lashever: If the FBI
were a private corporation,

28:08.721 --> 28:10.656
the agent who takes down
a criminal,

28:10.689 --> 28:12.258
agent responsible
for a raid

28:12.291 --> 28:13.692
would get
a piece of the pie.

28:13.726 --> 28:15.361
So just go take some.

28:15.394 --> 28:18.197
No wonder
you always get caught.

28:18.230 --> 28:20.366
Actually,
I almost never get caught.

28:20.399 --> 28:23.602
I stole $11,000
at that hotel yesterday.

28:23.635 --> 28:27.539
That's not even why
I'm wearing these.

28:27.573 --> 28:30.042
You did not.

